Any public entity may apply to the cabinet to obtain a No Further Remediation Letter, created by KRS 224.1-465, for a property. The application shall contain the following information:
A legal description of the property;
A copy of the deed for the property;
An environmental site assessment of the site sufficient to characterize the extent of any contamination of the site;
A proposed plan to remediate the environmental contamination upon the site; and
The proposed use of the property intended by the public entity after obtaining the No Further Remediation Letter.
